{
  "stem": "15193.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things became worse in Kaukehmen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father and my mother, they had to give up their business, and they had to get out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we always felt, after, that East Prussia was the birthplace of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We always had felt it, after a while.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so my sister and I, and another sister from [NON-ENGLISH], Dora, who joined us in Berlin, we insisted that my parents come to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we shared an apartment with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they brought along Ruth and Lea.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were the youngest.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Lea was only-- she was very, very young.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so Lea was about 14.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It wasn't long after, we had an invitation from the Jewish organization to attend a meeting where Mrs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Henrietta Szold, ?] from Israel, and Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Martin Buber were the speakers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My mother and I went.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the-- it was that they encouraged parents with children 15 and below to let them go to Israel, because they saw the handwriting on the wall.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they wanted to save these children from the terror of Adolf Hitler.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we first didn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't so much that we didn't, but it was so overwhelming.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for my parents to let my little, youngest sister of 15 go to Israel all by herself-- they were overwhelmed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we talked it over with the family, and we all decided, because for their safety and for their life, we let them go.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That must have been about 1934-- yes, 1934, 1935.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the meantime, my brother Paul, who had his own business in Vienna, felt anti-Semitism there, gave up his store, and went to a [HEBREW] in Denmark, to migrate to Israel.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
